snippet.textDisplay:
I will get the m8 before, but now I will definitely prefer a model 3 and the Porsche. Lighter, more grip/balance on corners are way more fun than heavy high torque beasts, for weekend back road runs! — I have a M5 to start with. Almost 2 tons. Fun! But not satisfying on trackday / autocross / twisty backroad , have to drive so carefully and can’t push too hard before entering, a S2K smokes me on S roads, although I easily pickup on straight lines. Also, it burns much more expensive tires and brakes waaaaay faster than lighter sports cars!!! Not saying it’s a bad car, it’s super good family car, but just not suitable for trackday/back road weekend drives! It’s Great for cruising! A nice sunny day in the forest or along the beach, and straight line crushing, and yeh, drifting. But when you want lateral G and feel the crazy grip and balance, that Tesla and Porsche are really hard to beat.
btw I also have a golf R which can beat that S2K, now I drive it for weekends when meet up with these light bastards, so cheap to maintain and so much fun cornering, so good to feel light! but when I want that horse power I took out the m5 and go to some highway entrance.
Next I just need some better (real) sports car. Things like Miata, Tesla 3, Porsche gt3/GT4, M2, I don’t know, don’t have the cash to get all of them, but still want all of them! 😂
